DataElement.preferredDefinition: An activity that produces an effect, or that is intended to alter the course of a disease in a patient or population. This is a general term that encompasses the medical, social, behavioral, and environmental acts that can have preventive, therapeutic, or palliative effects.:Available in place of something else.:The words or language units by which a thing is known._A condition or state at a particular time.:A system, often of numbered categories, for representation of data._The code that describes the state of this intervention alternate name.
